I"ñ<h2 id="how-to-run-simulations-in-these-pedagogic-modules">How to run Simulations in these Pedagogic Modules</h2>

<p>When going through these pedagogic modules you will be instructed to run a particular simulation tool. This is done via
a Web application and there are two cases:</p>

<p><strong>Case #1: You have been pointed to a static Web site that hosts the Web application</strong> (for instance by an instructor in a course): just go to that Web site.</p>

<p><strong>Case #2: You have not been pointed to a static Web site</strong>: In this case, you must run the Web app on your machine and go to a locally-hosted Web site</p>

<div class="ui accordion fluid">
<div class="title">
<i class="dropdown icon"></i>
(see instructions for Case #2)
</div>
<div class="ui segment content">

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Option #1: Run <a href="https://docker.com">Docker</a> directly on your machine</strong>:
        <ol>
          <li>install Docker:
            <ul>
              <li><a href="https://docs.docker.com/install/linux/docker-ce/ubuntu/">Instructions for Linux</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://docs.docker.com/docker-for-mac/install/">Instructions for macOS</a></li>
              <li><a href="https://docs.docker.com/docker-for-windows/install/">Instructions forW indows 10 Pro</a></li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>In a terminal type <code class="highlighter-rouge">docker pull wrenchproject/wrench-pedagogic-modules:activity-visualization</code></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>Then type <code class="highlighter-rouge">docker container run -p 3000:3000 -d  wrenchproject/wrench-pedagogic-modules:activity-visualization</code></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>Open a Web browser on your machine and navigate to <a href="localhost:3000/">localhost:3000/</a></p>
          </li>
          <li>When you are finished with the Web application in that same terminal type <code class="highlighter-rouge">docker kill $(docker ps -a -q  --filter ancestor=wrenchproject/wrench-pedagogic-modules:ics332-activity-visualization)</code></li>
        </ol>
      </li>
      <li><strong>Option #2: Run Docker within a <a href="https://www.vagrantup.com/">Vagrant</a> Virtual Machine</strong>:
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p>Install <a href="https://www.virtualbox.org/">VirtualBox</a></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>Install <a href="https://www.vagrantup.com/downloads.html">Vagrant binary</a></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>Download this <a href="/wrench-pedagogic-modules/public/Vagrantfile">Vagrantfile</a></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>In a terminal, navigate to the same directory where the <code class="highlighter-rouge">Vagrantfile</code>
from step 3 is located and run the command <code class="highlighter-rouge">vagrant up</code> (which may take
a few minutes)</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>Then, in that same directory, type <code class="highlighter-rouge">vagrant ssh</code>, which will give you a prompt in a terminal</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>In this terminal type <code class="highlighter-rouge">docker pull wrenchproject/wrench-pedagogic-modules:activity-visualization</code></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>Then type <code class="highlighter-rouge">docker container run -p 3000:3000 -d  wrenchproject/wrench-pedagogic-modules:activity-visualization</code></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>Open a Web browser on your machine and navigate to <a href="localhost:3000/">localhost:3000/</a></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>When you are finished with the Web application in that same terminal type <code class="highlighter-rouge">docker kill $(docker ps -a -q  --filter ancestor=wrenchproject/wrench-pedagogic-modules:ics332-activity-visualization)</code></p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </li>
    </ul>

  </div>
</div>

<hr />

<p>Once you have navigated to the appropriate Web site, then you simply:</p>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p>Sign in using your academic Google e-mail address (e.g., <code class="highlighter-rouge">&lt;UH Username&gt;@hawaii.edu</code>)</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Select whatever simulation tool you were instructed to run</p>
  </li>
</ul>

